FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1779354384
OL,3,CSummerland families begin legal
OL,4,Cchallenge to reopen inquests
OL,6,FThe families of the victims are
OL,7,Fchallenging a decision from the Isle
OL,8,Fof Man's Attorney General not to
OL,9,Fcommission new inquests to re-examine
OL,10,Fthe cause of death in May 2025.
OL,12,FJacqueline Hallam, who lost her best
OL,13,Ffriend and mother in the fire, lodged
OL,14,Fa claim against the AG's decision on
OL,15,Fbehalf of the Justice for Summerland
OL,16,Fcampaign, with the case due to be
OL,17,Fheard over two days.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1779354384
OL,3,CSummerland families begin legal
OL,4,Cchallenge to reopen inquests
OL,6,FAfter a minute's silence at Douglas
OL,7,FCourthouse, the lawyer representing
OL,8,Fthe families, Steven Coren, told the
OL,9,Fcourt how families have continued to
OL,10,Ffeel a sense of injustice.
OL,12,FHe said: "The verdict of misadventure
OL,13,Fhas caused and continues to cause
OL,14,Fsignificant offence among the families
OL,15,Fand the survivors, and the relatives
OL,16,Fof the survivors."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1779354384
OL,3,CSummerland families begin legal
OL,4,Cchallenge to reopen inquests
OL,6,FMr Corren said the ruling in the
OL,7,Fcampaigner's favour would go some way
OL,8,Fto "remove the stain that innocent
OL,9,Fmembers of the public who were
OL,10,Fattending Summerland were in some way
OL,11,Fresponsible for their own deaths".
OL,13,FSome of the families were present in
OL,14,Fcourt today, visibly emotional as key
OL,15,Faspects of the disaster were picked
OL,16,Fapart.
OL,18,FThe fire ripped through the leisure
OL,19,Fcomplex in just 20 minutes, causing 50
OL,20,Fdeaths and lifelong injuries.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1779354384
OL,3,CSummerland families begin legal
OL,4,Cchallenge to reopen inquests
OL,6,FMr Corren argued that new scientific
OL,7,Fforensic investigations would, in the
OL,8,Fcampaign's view, undoubtedly lead to a
OL,9,Fdifferent outcome.
OL,11,FHe cited recent examples of other
OL,12,Ftragedies including the Hillsborough
OL,13,Fdisaster and the 1981 Stardust
OL,14,Fnightclub fire, in which 48 people
OL,15,Fdied during a Valentine's Day disco in
OL,16,FDublin.
OL,18,FIn both cases, fresh inquests
OL,19,Foverturned the original verdicts.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1779354384
OL,3,CSummerland families begin legal
OL,4,Cchallenge to reopen inquests
OL,6,FMr Coren said it was "inevitable" that
OL,7,Fa fresh inquest into Summerland would
OL,8,Fhave a different outcome, citing
OL,9,Ftechnological advancements and expert
OL,10,Ftestimony.
OL,12,FOliver Helfrich, representing the AG's
OL,13,Fchambers, said that a retrospective
OL,14,Fclaim would not be successful given
OL,15,Fthe time that had elapsed.
OL,17,FHe also argued that for every family
OL,18,Fwho believed a fresh inquest would be
OL,19,Fbeneficial, there are more who feel it
OL,20,Fwould only reopen old wounds.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1779354384
OL,3,CSummerland families begin legal
OL,4,Cchallenge to reopen inquests
OL,6,FHe also highlighted the key
OL,7,Fdifferences between the Summerland
OL,8,Fdisaster and those that took place at
OL,9,FHillsborough and in Dublin. He argued
OL,10,Fthis particular case should be seen
OL,11,Fthrough the lens of the Isle of Man.
OL,13,FIt will be down to a Manx judge, known
OL,14,Fas a Deemster, to make the final
OL,15,Fdecision, with the hearing set to
OL,16,Fcontinue on Thursday 21 May.
OL,18,FWant more on the issues affecting the
OL,19,FNorth? Our podcast, From the North
OL,20,Fanswers the questions that matter to
OL,21,Four region.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/7
